I'm having trouble wording one of my scripts. Here it is...

[code:1ba33qma]if (this&#46;cursecount = 105) {
(&quot;&quot;)
if (not player&#46;hairlength = &quot;long&quot;) {
}
else {
SetTo(&quot;hairlength&quot;, &quot;long&quot;)
}
}[/code:1ba33qma]

Now this is okay of itself, but my question is....er...okay. Here's a better way of stating this...

player.hairlength: buzzed 0, short 1, shoulder length 2, [b:1ba33qma]long 3[/b:1ba33qma], very long 4, extremely long 5, dragging on the ground long 6.

Here are the variables (listed above). The script will make any hairlength turn into the one marked in bold. So I was wondering, how would I put that in a msg(&quot;&quot;). Like if the player's hair is longer than &quot;long&quot;, I would want to describe it [i:1ba33qma]shrinking [/i:1ba33qma]in a message and if it's shorter, than I want to describe it in a message as [i:1ba33qma]growing[/i:1ba33qma]. 

I thought of doing...

[code:1ba33qma]if (player&#46;hairlength_as_int &gt;3) {
msg(&quot;your hair shrinks in length! Argh!&quot;)
SetTo(&quot;hairlength&quot;, &quot;long&quot;)
}
else if (player&#46;hairlength_as_int &lt;3) {
msg(&quot;your hair is growing, egads!&quot;)
SetTo(&quot;hairlength&quot;, &quot;long&quot;)
}
else {
if player&#46;hairlength_as_int = 3) {
msg (&quot;You feel something happening to your hair, but it turns out to be nothing&#46;&quot;)
}
}[/code:1ba33qma]

But for some reason (haven't tested it) I was thinking this wouldn't work. Any suggestions? I might not be focusing clearly though because I'm tired.

